-# locals: collection_id (String), sentinel (Sentinel|nil), groups (Array<[id, name]>),
-#         public_collection (Boolean)
-#
-# The Derivative access tab: authors this collection's Sentinel — the per-tier
-# read-group default applied to Works added under it. Two groups, because the
-# vocabulary has two shapes: the image renditions form a resolution ladder
-# (widest audience at top, narrowest at the bottom) so the monotonicity rule
-# reads as structure — audience narrows as you descend; the other renditions
-# (audio/video/pdf) gate independently, so they get a plain list with no rail.
-# The header carries a visibility chip for the collection itself, so the open
-# option can read uniformly as "Inherit from collection" — the chip is where
-# the author sees whether inheriting means public or restricted.
.py-2.px-1
  = bootstrap_form_tag(url: sentinel_collection_path(collection_id), method: :patch) do |f|
    .well.p-3.my-3.rounded-3
      .d-flex.align-items-center.flex-wrap.gap-2.mb-1
        %h5.mb-0 Derivative access default
        - if public_collection
          %span.badge.bg-success-subtle.text-success-emphasis.border.border-success-subtle
            %i.fa-solid.fa-globe.me-1{ 'aria-hidden' => 'true' }
            Public
        - else
          %span.badge.bg-secondary-subtle.text-secondary-emphasis.border.border-secondary-subtle
            %i.fa-solid.fa-lock.me-1{ 'aria-hidden' => 'true' }
            Restricted
      %p.small.text-muted.mb-0
        Each rendition of Works added to this collection inherits the collection's access unless
        you restrict it to groups — a rendition is never more visible than the collection. Image
        visibility must also narrow as resolution grows, so a rendition can't be more open than a
        smaller one above it. Audio, video, and PDF renditions gate on their own.
    %section.my-3{ data: { controller: "derivative-policy" } }
      %h6.derivative-group-heading Image renditions
      %ol.derivative-ladder.list-unstyled.mb-4
        - Sentinel::IMAGE_LADDER.each do |tier|
          = render "collections/derivative_tier", tier: tier, sentinel: sentinel, groups: groups
      %h6.derivative-group-heading Other renditions
      %ul.derivative-independent.list-unstyled.mb-0
        - Sentinel::INDEPENDENT.each do |tier|
          = render "collections/derivative_tier", tier: tier, sentinel: sentinel, groups: groups
    .well.p-3.my-3.rounded-3
      = f.button "Save default", type: :submit, class: "btn btn-success"
      = link_to "Cancel", collection_path(collection_id), class: "btn btn-warning"
